dc_title_s: Clay County, Iowa, 1949, aerial photomosaic index
dc_description_s: Title supplied by cataloger based on information from sheet labels. Images are photoreductions of mosaics created from original aerial photographs. Designating symbol BZK. Form of individual image numbering: BZK-1F-[number], BZK-2F-[number], BZK-3F-[number], or BZK-4F-[number]."Flying completed 9-9-49." Flown by Woltz Studios, Des Moines, Iowa."Approximate scale, 1:20,000" [refers to individual images from which mosaic was made].|Contact the Map Collection at The University of Iowa Libraries: http://www.lib.uiowa.edu/maps/contact/
